# Anime Dataset for Machine Learning

## 1. Title & Collection Method

### Title:

Anime Dataset for Rating Analysis and Classification

### Collection Method:

This dataset contains information about 50 anime titles. The data was collected manually by researching anime information from various public sources and recording details such as anime name, release year, genre, studio, and rating. The dataset was organized into a structured table for analysis and machine learning purposes.

## 2. Description of Features & Label

### Features (X):

1. Anime_Name – Name of the anime.
2. Release_Year – Year the anime was released.
3. Genre – Category of the anime (Action, Adventure, Fantasy, etc.).
4. Studio – Animation studio that produced the anime.
5. Rating – Average rating given by viewers.

### Label (y):

Rating

The rating is used as the target variable because it represents the outcome we want to analyze or predict based on the other features.

## 3. Dataset Structure

* Number of Rows: 50
* Number of Columns: 5

