## 4. Quality Issues

Several data quality issues may exist in the dataset:

* Missing values in some records.
* Different formatting styles for genre names.
* Possible duplicate anime entries.
* Categorical text values that need encoding.
* Ratings may vary depending on the source used.

These issues will require preprocessing before training a machine learning model.

## 5. Learning Type

This is a Supervised Learning problem because the dataset contains a clear target variable (Rating). The model can learn the relationship between the features and the rating to make predictions on new anime records.

## 6. Use Case

This dataset can be used in a machine learning project to predict anime ratings based on their characteristics such as genre, release year, and studio.

Possible applications include:

* Rating prediction (Regression).
* Classifying anime into high-rated and low-rated categories (Classification).
* Discovering similar anime groups based on features (Clustering).

Within the Data Science Lifecycle, this dataset belongs to the Data Collection stage. After collection, the data will move through preprocessing, analysis, model building, evaluation, and deployment stages.
